It shouldnâ€™t need to be stated so many times, but another reminder wonâ€™t hurt...â€if itâ€™s too cold for you, itâ€™s too cold for them!â€ PLEASE bring your pets inside during this weather or ensure they have proper and adequate protection from the elements if they cannot come inside your house. Your pets can get frostbite and hypothermia; these temperatures can kill. Determining a safe amount of time outside can vary based on the individual dog, but puppies and small dogs, senior dogs, and dogs with thin coats should only be outside for short periods of time.
Please contact your local authorities if you see signs of animal abuse or cruelty. Animal neglect is a crime in all 50 states. In states like PA, owners can now face felony charges for leaving pets outside in freezing temperatures over a certain amount of time. If you see a pet left in the cold, please speak up. ğŸ’›
